going to get us
part of the way we need to go?

31:20.879 --> 31:24.116 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GAVIN SCHMIDT, Director, NASA
Goddard Institute
for Space Studies: Well, like
the old proverb

31:24.149 --> 31:29.387 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
says, a journey of 1,000 miles
starts with
a single global agreement.

31:29.421 --> 31:31.156 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And this is where we're at.

31:31.189 --> 31:36.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have an agreement now that
encompasses
-- that's in effect that
encompasses every

31:36.428 --> 31:38.263 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
country in the world.

31:38.296 --> 31:41.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every country in the world is
thinking that
this is something that they need
to get behind.

31:41.967 --> 31:50.108 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every country has promised to
reduce emissions
to the level that they signed up
for.

31:50.142 --> 31:55.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
While President Obama is correct
that, in
and of itself, this is not going
to stop global

31:55.647 --> 31:59.184 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
warming, that's a much bigger
task.

31:59.217 --> 32:01.520 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But this is a step in that right
direction.

32:01.553 --> 32:09.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what the hope is, is that,
with experience,
with seeing the best practices
that other

32:09.594 --> 32:15.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
countries have adopted, great
ideas, new technologies,
that people will be able to
increase their

32:15.700 --> 32:21.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
commitments under this agreement
at each of
the next update stages, which
come every few

32:21.406 --> 32:23.208 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
years.

32:23.241 --> 32:25.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But how do you --
how confident
are you, though, that you are
going to be

32:25.644 --> 32:31.249 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
able to even take that baby
step, when you
still have critics out there
saying things

32:31.283 --> 32:36.988 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
