fuels.

32:44.596 --> 32:48.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are going to be jobs
created in new
technologies that are more
efficient.

32:48.400 --> 32:55.340 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are many different things
that are happening,
both in building resiliency to
future climate

32:55.373 --> 33:01.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
change, but also building the
infrastructure
of the future that is ongoing
right now.

33:01.913 --> 33:09.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think you can get a little bit
caught up
with the supposed balance
between the economy

33:09.287 --> 33:10.922 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or the environment.

33:10.956 --> 33:14.926 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that these things
actually aren't
opposed, for the most part.

33:14.960 --> 33:19.497 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, this week,
Gavin Schmidt,
we saw one of the world's most
important sites

33:19.531 --> 33:26.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
