in the 19th century, was 280
parts per million;

33:53.031 --> 33:59.337 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
400 parts per million is a 40
percent increase
over that, and this is a level
that hasn't

33:59.371 --> 34:05.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been seen in the climate since
